{{Infobox album| | name = Bill Cosby Talks to Kids About Drugs | type = studio | artist = [[Bill Cosby]] [[The Cosby Kids]] | cover = Bill Cosby Talks to Kids About Drugs.jpeg | alt = | released = November 10, 1971 | recorded = 1971 | venue = | studio = | genre = [[Children]] | length = 32:33 | label = [[Uni Records]] | producer = | prev_title = [[Badfoot Brown & the Bunions Bradford Funeral & Marching Band]] | prev_year = 1971 | next_title = [[Bill Cosby Presents Badfoot Brown & the Bunions Bradford Funeral Marching Band]] | next_year = 1972 }}
'''''Bill Cosby Talks to Kids About Drugs''''' (1971) is an album by [[Bill Cosby]]. Unlike most of [[Bill Cosby#Albums|his recordings]], this is not a full-fledged comedy album, but rather a record intended for children to school them on the dangers of [[Recreational drug use|drugs]] through songs and dialogue. It won the [[Grammy Awards of 1972|Grammy Award in 1972]] for [[Grammy Award for Best Album for Children|Best Recording for Children]].
The album was available for some time to download free on [[Andy Baio|Waxy.org]]. Cosby's lawyers eventually had the album download removed via a [[cease and desist]] letter.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://wiredblogs.tripod.com/monkeybites/index.blog?entry_id=1426957 | title = Waxy vs. The Cos | accessdate = 2012-03-30 | last = Calore | first = Michael | date = 2006-03-03 | work = Monkey Bites | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20060614192431/http://wiredblogs.tripod.com/monkeybites/index.blog?entry_id=1426957 | archivedate = 2006-06-14}}</ref>
