==Production and broadcast== ''Go-Go Boy Interrupted'' premiered on [[YouTube]] in October 2014.<ref name="Advocate 2014-10"/><ref name="Towleroad 1-2">{{cite web |url=http://www.towleroad.com/2014/10/what-happens-when-a-go-go-boy-ages-out-of-his-career-and-has-to-start-over-video.html |title=''Go-Go Boy Interrupted'' Episodes 1 & 2 |work=Towleroad |first=Sean |last=Mandell |date=October 15, 2014 |accessdate=November 24, 2014}}</ref><ref name="HP Profile"/> Fowlie commented on each of the first seven episodes via a column at HuffingtonPost.com as they were released.<ref name="HP Profile">{{cite web |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/jimmy-fowlie/ |title=Jimmy Fowlie Profile |work=The Huffington Post |accessdate=November 23, 2014}}</ref>
A [[Kickstarter]] [[crowdfunding]] campaign ending in October 2015 was established to fund a potential second season,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/heres-what-happens-to-a-go-go-boy-when-he-has-to-grow-up_55eef258e4b03784e2767287 |title=Here's What Happens To A Go-Go Boy When He Has To Grow Up |work=The Huffington Post |first=JamesMichael |last=Nichols |date=September 8, 2015 |accessdate=September 11, 2015}}</ref><ref name="Kickstarter 2">{{cite web|url=https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/1043396910/go-go-boy-interrupted-season-2 |title=''Go-Go Boy Interrupted'' Season 2 |publisher=[[Kickstarter]] |accessdate=September 11, 2015}}</ref> and 450 contributors raised $69,033 for the project.<ref name="Kickstarter 2"/> [[Towleroad]] reported in September 2015 that Droege, Stewart and Evans would return alongside new additions including [[Heather Morris]], [[Briga Heelan]], [[Chris Riggi]], [[Willam Belli]], [[Nick Adams (theatre actor)|Nick Adams]], [[Karen Maruyama]] and [[Fortune Feimster]].<ref name="Towleroad Ssn 2">{{cite web |url=http://www.towleroad.com/2015/09/go-go-boy-interrupted-returns-seeks-funding-for-raucous-season-2-on-kickstarter-video/ |title=''Go-Go Boy Interrupted'' Returns, Seeks Funding for Raucous Season 2 on Kickstarter |work=Towleroad |first=Sean |last=Mandell |date=September 20, 2015 |accessdate=September 21, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.queerty.com/this-go-go-boy-doesnt-want-to-stop-dancing-for-you-20150911 |title=This Go-Go Boy Doesn’t Want To Stop Dancing For You |website=Queerty |first=Justin |last=Hernandez |date=September 11, 2015 |accessdate=September 21, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://gogoboyinterrupted.com/season-two-cast-and-crew/ |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160129084630/http://gogoboyinterrupted.com/season-two-cast-and-crew/ |accessdate=March 21, 2016 |archivedate=January 29, 2016 |title=Season 2 Cast and Crew |publisher=GoGoBoyInterrupted.com}}</ref>
Season 2 premiered on April 12, 2016, with a new episode following on each Tuesday for 14 weeks.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/go-go-boy-interrupted-season-two_us_56e826dee4b0b25c918345e5 |title=Here's What Happens To A Go-Go Boy When He Grows Up |work=The Huffington Post |first=JamesMichael |last=Nichols |date=March 15, 2016 |accessdate=March 21, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.out.com/music/2016/3/15/watch-jimmy-fowlie-releases-season-2-teaser-go-go-boy-interrupted |title=WATCH: Jimmy Fowlie Releases Season 2 Teaser of ''Go-Go Boy Interrupted'' |work=[[Out (magazine)|Out]] |first=Glenn |last=Garner |date=March 15, 2016 |accessdate=March 21, 2016}}</ref>
==Reception== Daniel Reynolds of ''[[The Advocate (LGBT magazine)|The Advocate]]'' praised ''Go-Go Boy Interrupted'' as "hilarious" and "uproarious",<ref name="Advocate 2014-10"/> and Sean Mandell of Towleroad called the series "irreverent".<ref name="HP Fowlie 4"/><ref name="HP Fowlie 5"/><ref name="HP Fowlie 6"/><ref name="HP Fowlie 7"/> TheGayUK called it "wonderfully hilarious" and a "delightfully entertaining slice of West Hollywood gay life."<ref name="GayUK">{{cite web |url=http://www.thegayuk.com/magazine/4574334751/Three-Of-The-Best-Gay-TV-Web-Series-Pick-Of-The-Week/9103893? |title=Three Of The Best Gay TV Web Series, Pick Of The Week |website=TheGayUK |date=November 27, 2014 |accessdate=January 10, 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141204023012/http://www.thegayuk.com/magazine/4574334751/Three-Of-The-Best-Gay-TV-Web-Series-Pick-Of-The-Week/9103893 |archivedate=December 4, 2014 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref>
The series won the 2017 ''[[Queerty]]'' Award for Best Web Series.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.queerty.com/winner-2017-queerty-award-winners-announed-20170222 |title=And the winners of the 2017 Queerties are... |first=David |last=Reddish |date=February 22, 2017 |work=Queerty |accessdate=February 23, 2017}}</ref>
