{{Infobox comics creator | name = Ted Naifeh | image = 10.5.17TedNaifehByLuigiNovi1.jpg | caption = Naifeh at the 2017 [[New York Comic Con]] | birth_name = | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = American | write = Y | pencil = Y | ink = Y | alias = | signature = <!-- very optional --> | notable works = ''[[Gloomcookie]]'' | awards = | website = | subcat = American }} '''Edward "Ted" Naifeh''' is an American [[comic book writer]] and [[artist]] known for his illustrations in the goth romance comic ''[[Gloomcookie]]''.<ref>[http://www.popimage.com/content/viewnews.cgi?newsid1049699286,95359, "How Loathsome Interview with Tristan & Ted"]. PopImage.</ref> Naifeh has since become most known as the creator of the [[Eisner Award|Eisner-Award]]-nominated series ''[[Courtney Crumrin]]'', published by [[Oni Press]].<ref>[http://www.fangoria.com/new/courtney-crumrin-tales-of-a-warlock-comic-book-review/ “COURTNEY CRUMRIN: TALES OF A WARLOCK” (Comic Book Review)]</ref>
Other works by Naifeh include ''[[How Loathsome]]'', which he co-created with [[Tristan Crane]]; the comic adaptation of the [[PlayStation Portable|PSP]] game ''[[Death, Jr.]]'' (written by [[Gary Whitta]]); three issues of the comic adaptation of [[Gene Wolfe]]'s [[The Shadow of the Torturer]], [[Seven Seas Entertainment]]'s ''[[Unearthly (manga)|Unearthly]]''; and the [[Oni Press]] series ''[[Polly and the Pirates]]''. Naifeh also provided illustrations for [[Caitlín R. Kiernan]]'s short-fiction collection, ''[[Alabaster (book)|Alabaster]]''.<ref>[http://www.popimage.com/content/viewnews.cgi?newsid1014766670,90656, Interview @ PopImage, Feb.02]</ref> Ted is currently illustrating Good Neighbors, a trilogy of graphic novels written by [[Holly Black]] and published through [[Scholastic Corporation|Scholastic]].<ref>[http://www.bdtheque.com/interview-ted-naifeh-vo-32.html Interview @ bdtheque.com, April.07]</ref>
Naifeh has illustrated cards for the ''[[Magic: The Gathering]]'' collectible card game.<ref>[http://blog.newsarama.com/2009/08/25/tednaifehcom-v-20/, Interview with Newsarama, August 2009]</ref>
